'''Marco Friedl''' (born 16 March 1998) is an Austrian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Bundesliga]] club [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]], which he [[captain (association football)|captains]], and the [[Austria national football team|Austria national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{Soccerway|414367|accessdate=18 August 2017}}</ref>

==Club career==

===Youth career===
Friedl began his youth career at hometown club SV Kirchbichl in 2002, before moving to fellow Austrian club [[FC Kufstein]] in 2007. In 2008, he moved to the [[FC Bayern Munich Junior Team|youth academy]] of German club [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fcbayern.com/de/teams/profis/marco-friedl |title=Marco Friedl |website=fcbayern.com |publisher=[[FC Bayern Munich|FC Bayern München AG]] |access-date=18 August 2017 |language=German |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201034009/https://fcbayern.com/de/teams/profis/marco-friedl |archive-date=1 December 2017}}</ref>

In 2017, Friedl won the 2016–17 [[Under 19 Bundesliga|A-Junioren Bundesliga Süd/Südwest]] with Bayern's under-19 team, scoring five goals during the season.<ref name="soccerway"/> The team went on to advance to the final of the A-Junioren Bundesliga championship round, before losing to [[Borussia Dortmund Youth Sector|Borussia Dortmund]] 8–7 on penalties.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/match-report/ma8397450/lineup/ |title=Borussia Dortmund – Bayern München 8:7 (Youth Championship 2017, Final) |website=WorldFootball.net |publisher=HEIM:SPIEL Medien GmbH & Co. KG |date=22 May 2017 |access-date=18 August 2017}}</ref>

===Bayern Munich===
Friedl began his senior career with [[FC Bayern Munich II|Bayern Munich II]] in the [[2015–16 Regionalliga|2015–16 season]], making his debut in the [[Regionalliga Bayern]] on 22 November 2015 in a 2–0 [[Munich derby|derby]] loss against [[TSV 1860 Munich II|1860 Munich II]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/match-report/ma2409663/lineup/ |title=TSV 1860 München II – Bayern München II 2:0 (Regionalliga Bayern 2015/2016, 20. Round) |website=WorldFootball.net |publisher=HEIM:SPIEL Medien GmbH & Co. KG |date=22 November 2015 |access-date=18 August 2017}}</ref>

On 14 March 2017, Friedl signed his first professional contract with Bayern, lasting from 1 July 2017 through 30 June 2021.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2017/03/fcb-sign-marco-friedl |title=Pro terms for Marco Friedl |website=fcbayern.com |publisher=[[FC Bayern Munich|FC Bayern München AG]] |date=15 March 2017 |access-date=18 August 2017}}</ref>

Friedl scored his first goal for Bayern Munich II in the Regionalliga Bayern on 27 October 2017, opening the scoring in a 1–1 home draw against [[FV Illertissen]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/match-report/ma8420152/lineup/ |title=Bayern München II – FV Illertissen 1:1 (Regionalliga Bayern 2017/2018, 18. Round) |website=WorldFootball.net |publisher=HEIM:SPIEL Medien GmbH & Co. KG |date=27 October 2017 |access-date=27 October 2017}}</ref>

Friedl began his first team career with Bayern Munich in the [[2017–18 FC Bayern Munich season|2017–18 season]], making his professional debut as a starter in the [[UEFA Champions League]] on 22 November 2017 in a [[2017–18 UEFA Champions League group stage#Anderlecht v Bayern Munich|2–1 away win]] against [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2021661--anderlecht-vs-bayern-munchen/ |title=UEFA Champions League – Anderlecht-Bayern |website=[[UEFA]] |publisher=[[UEFA|Union of European Football Associations]] |date=22 November 2017 |access-date=22 November 2017}}</ref> Three days later, Friedl made his league debut for the first team when he came on as a half-time substitute for [[James Rodríguez]] in the [[Bundesliga]] away match against [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]], which finished as a 1–2 loss for Bayern.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/match-report/ma8417607/lineup/ |title=Bor. Mönchengladbach – Bayern München 2:1 (Bundesliga 2017/2018, 13. Round) |website=WorldFootball.net |publisher=HEIM:SPIEL Medien GmbH & Co. KG |date=25 November 2017 |access-date=25 January 2018}}</ref>

===Werder Bremen (loan)===
On 25 January 2018, Friedl signed with [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]] on an 18-month loan deal from Bayern Munich without an option to buy, lasting until 30 June 2019.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://fcbayern.com/de/news/2018/01/friedl-wechselt-auf-leihbasis-nach-bremen |title=Friedl wechselt auf Leihbasis nach Bremen |trans-title=Friedl moves to Bremen on loan |website=fcbayern.com |publisher=[[FC Bayern Munich|FC Bayern München AG]] |date=25 January 2018 |access-date=25 January 2018 |language=German}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.werder.de/en/news/news/werder-bremen-news/20172018/marco-friedl-loan-25012018/ |title=Marco Friedl joins Werder on loan |website=werder.de |publisher=[[SV Werder Bremen|SV Werder Bremen GmbH & Co. KGaA]] |date=25 January 2018 |access-date=25 January 2018 |archive-date=29 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190529102814/https://www.werder.de/en/news/news/werder-bremen-news/20172018/marco-friedl-loan-25012018 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Kohfeldt: "Wir müssen jetzt zupacken" |url=https://www.kicker.de/kohfeldt_wir-muessen-jetzt-zupacken-715836/artikel |access-date=27 January 2018 |work=kicker Online |date=25 January 2018 |language=German}}</ref>

===Werder Bremen===
[[File:MarcoFriedl werder bremen (cropped).jpg|thumb|Friedl with [[Werder Bremen]] in 2018]]
In May 2019, Werder Bremen announced the permanent signing of Friedl for the 2019–20 season. Friedl agreed a "long-term" contract with the club.<ref>{{cite web |title=Marco Friedl bleibt bei Werder Bremen |url=https://www.butenunbinnen.de/sport/werder-verpflichtet-freidl-100.html |website=buten un binnen |publisher=Radio Bremen |accessdate=29 May 2019 |language=German |date=29 May 2019 |archive-date=29 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190529121944/https://www.butenunbinnen.de/sport/werder-verpflichtet-freidl-100.html |url-status=dead }}</ref> The transfer fee was reported as €3 million<ref>{{cite web |title=Friedls Wünsche: Stammplatz, Europa - und Gregoritsch |url=https://www.kicker.de/friedls-wuensche_stammplatz-europa---und-gregoritsch-752991/artikel |website=kicker Online |access-date=9 July 2019 |language=German |date=9 July 2019}}</ref> or up to €3.5 million including possible bonuses,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bürger |first1=Malte |title=Friedl-Wechsel endgültig perfekt |url=https://www.weser-kurier.de/sport_artikel,-friedlwechsel-endgueltig-perfekt-_arid,1833712.html |accessdate=9 July 2019 |work=Weser Kurier |date=3 June 2019 |language=German}}</ref> depending on the source.

Friedl scored his first Bundesliga goal on the sixth matchday of the season, against [[Borussia Dortmund]] in a 2–2 draw.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Pearson |first1=Matt |title=Bundesliga: Borussia Dortmund squander lead to spirited Bremen |url=https://www.dw.com/en/bundesliga-borussia-dortmund-squander-lead-to-spirited-bremen/a-50621611 |website=Deutsche Welle |accessdate=30 September 2019 |date=28 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Borussia Dortmund 2-2 Werder Bremen: Hosts miss chance to move second in Bundesliga |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/49865162 |website=BBC Sport |accessdate=30 September 2019 |date=28 September 2019}}</ref>

In July 2022, following Werder Bremen's return to the Bundesliga in the [[2021–22 SV Werder Bremen season|2021–22 season]], Friedl agreed a contract extension with the club.<ref>{{cite web |title=Verlängerung fix: Marco Friedl sieht Zukunft beim SV Werder |url=https://www.kicker.de/verlaengerung-fix-friedl-sieht-zukunft-beim-sv-werder-907478/artikel |website=kicker |access-date=3 July 2022 |language=de |date=1 July 2022}}</ref> Later that month, he was named as the club's captain ahead of the [[2022–23 SV Werder Bremen season|2022–23 season]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.werder.de/aktuell/news/profis/20222023/pm-marco-24072022/ |title=Entscheidung gefallen: Marco Friedl ist neuer Werder-Kapitän |publisher=SV Werder Bremen |language=de |date=24 July 2022 }}</ref> In April 2025, he extended his contract with the club.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.werder.de/aktuell/news/profis/2024/25/pm-vvl-friedl-18042025/ |title=Der Kapitän bleibt an Bord |publisher=SV Werder Bremen |language=de |date=18 April 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==

===Youth===
After progressing through the youth teams, Friedl made his [[Austria national under-21 football team|Austria under-21]] debut on 8 June 2017 in a [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification|qualification]] match for the [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]] against [[Gibraltar national under-21 football team|Gibraltar]]. He opened the scoring in the 6th minute in the [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification Group 7#Austria v Gibraltar|3–0 home win]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/match/2022454--austria-vs-gibraltar/ |title=Under-21 – Austria-Gibraltar |website=[[UEFA]] |publisher=[[UEFA|Union of European Football Associations]] |date=8 June 2017 |access-date=18 August 2017}}</ref>

===Senior===
Friedl made his [[Austria national football team|national team]] debut on 7 October 2020 in a friendly against [[Greece national football team|Greece]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ESPN]]|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match?gameId=573995|title=Austria v Greece game report|date=7 October 2020}}</ref>

